Citation.sTitle: Equilibrium Study in the KNO3 + NH4NO3 + H2O System at Temperatures from 293.15 to 323.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: A solid-liquid equilibrium (SLE) study was conducted in the ternary system KNO3 + NH4NO3 + H2O using the isothermal solution saturation method at temperatures of 293.15 K, 303.15 K, 313.15 K and 323.15 K. The experimental data obtained were used to plot a section of the solubility polytherm of the investigated system and show the dependence of the densities of equilibrium solutions on their chemical compositions. It has been found that a complex salt of the formula K0.33(NH4)0.66NO3 is formed in the system at a temperature below 303.15 K.
